notes.note: Rep from Bruce Hyundai Nova Scotia called in, customer was driving and started to experience violent side to side vibration. Took in for diag. Determined right side cv shaft failed internally, which also damaged intermediate shaft as it popped out slightly and destroyed splines. Going to submit an estimate for repair. M.P.
notes.content: Rep from Bruce Hyundai Nova Scotia called in, customer was driving and started to experience violent side to side vibration. Took in for diag. Determined right side cv shaft failed internally, which also damaged intermediate shaft as it popped out slightly and destroyed splines. Going to submit an estimate for repair. M.P.

notes.note: Rec'd estimate, rep says they do not have access to after market parts, thought that was odd. Inquired further. Noticed pricing for half shaft (which I can see not being able to get after market) was higher than msrp from part catelog online. Inquired about that. Also asked to verify requested labour hours. No listing for half shaft/axle bearing labour on Mitchell. Will have to inquire further. M.P.
notes.content: Rec'd estimate, rep says they do not have access to after market parts, thought that was odd. Inquired further. Noticed pricing for half shaft (which I can see not being able to get after market) was higher than msrp from part catelog online. Inquired about that. Also asked to verify requested labour hours. No listing for half shaft/axle bearing labour on Mitchell. Will have to inquire further. M.P.

notes.note: Rep emailed back, confirmed 2.0 hours for replacement of rf cv shaft and intermediate shaft. Called Hyundai Mississauga, confirmed 2.0 hours for replacement of both items is sufficient. Confirmed part pricing $799.05. Quoted price of $807.25 good. Proceeding with claim. M.P.
notes.content: Rep emailed back, confirmed 2.0 hours for replacement of rf cv shaft and intermediate shaft. Called Hyundai Mississauga, confirmed 2.0 hours for replacement of both items is sufficient. Confirmed part pricing $799.05. Quoted price of $807.25 good. Proceeding with claim. M.P.

notes.note:
Hey Monica, wow I am surprised. Not much we can do about that, all we can do is proceed with the oem parts and get this customer back on the road! Thank you for clarifying the labour hours, I just wanted to be sure so that there is no confusion as I know some shops charge 0.5 hours for diag and 1.5 for the alignment etc. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for diagnostic and the alignment, as well as a $100 deductible. Additionally, we pay out a maximum of $130/h for labour, so if you choose to charge $135/h, the difference will be the responsibility of the customer. The payout is as follows:

Parts-$1506.75
Labour-$260.00 (2.0 hours x $130/h)
Deductible-$100.00
Tax-$250.01
Authorization-CINUWINQY9

Total = $1916.76

Once the repair is complete, please send us a copy of the final invoice for payment. Our accounts payable department will reach out within 2 business days of receiving the invoice for payment over the phone via credit card.

Best regards, 


Matthew Puls
Claims Adjuster
